EDIT CONFIGURATION FILE

This screen allows you to edit the configuration file ("runrepl.opt")
for a Replicator Server.

The box on the left shows the lines of the current file.  You can add
parameters by simply typing them in on the left or by using the
SelectFlag operation.

The columns on the right are:

        COLUMN NAME     DESCRIPTION
        -----------     -----------
        Flag            A server startup parameter or flag.

        Description     A short description of the startup parameter.


The menu commands are as follows:

        MENU COMMAND    SYNOPSIS
        ------------    --------
        WriteFile       Write the contents of the left box to the
                        configuration file.

        Default         Replace the contents of the left box with the
                        set of default parameters appropriate for the
                        current server.

        SelectFlag      Add the currently highlighted flag to the end of
                        the left box.  You may have to edit the flag
                        further by adding parameter values.

        DescribeFlag    Display a long description of the startup
                        parameter and acceptable parameter values in a
                        popup message box.

        ListChoices     Display a list of acceptable values for those
                        parameters having a fixed set of values.

        Help            Access the Help facility.

        End             Return to the Replication Monitor screen.
